verses.text: Then we turned , and went up the way to Bashan : and Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people , to battle at Edrei.

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto me, Fear him not: for I will deliver him, and all his people , and his land , into thy hand ; and thou shalt do unto him as thou didst unto Sihon king of the Amorites , which dwelt at Heshbon.
So the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God delivered into our hands Og also, the king of Bashan , and all his people : and we smote him until none was left to him remaining.
And we took all his cities at that time , there was not a city which we took not from them, threescore cities , all the region of Argob , the kingdom of Og in Bashan.
All these cities \add were\add* fenced with high walls , gates , and bars ; beside unwalled towns a great many.
And we utterly destroyed them, as we did unto Sihon king of Heshbon , utterly destroying the men , women , and children , of every city.
But all the cattle , and the spoil of the cities , we took for a prey to ourselves.
And we took at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites the land that \add was\add* on this side Jordan , from the river of Arnon unto mount Hermon ;
(\add Which\add* Hermon the Sidonians call Sirion ; and the Amorites call it Shenir ;)
All the cities of the plain , and all Gilead , and all Bashan , unto Salchah and Edrei , cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.

For only Og king of Bashan remained of the remnant of giants ; behold, his bedstead \add was\add* a bedstead of iron ; \add is\add* it not in Rabbath of the children of Ammon ? nine cubits \add was\add* the length thereof, and four cubits the breadth of it, after the cubit of a man. \p

And this land , \add which\add* we possessed at that time , from Aroer , which \add is\add* by the river Arnon , and half mount Gilead , and the cities thereof, gave I unto the Reubenites and to the Gadites.
And the rest of Gilead , and all Bashan , \add being\add* the kingdom of Og , gave I unto the half tribe of Manasseh ; all the region of Argob , with all Bashan , which was called the land of giants.
Jair the son of Manasseh took all the country of Argob unto the coasts of Geshuri and Maachathi ; and called them after his own name , Bashan-havoth-jair , unto this day.
And I gave Gilead unto Machir.

And unto the Reubenites and unto the Gadites I gave from Gilead even unto the river Arnon half the valley , and the border even unto the river Jabbok , \add which is\add* the border of the children of Ammon ;

The plain also, and Jordan , and the coast \add thereof\add*, from Chinnereth even unto the sea of the plain , \add even\add* the salt sea , under Ashdoth-pisgah eastward.\f + \fr 3.17 \ft Ashdoth-pisgah: or, the springs of Pisgah, or, the hill\f* \p

¶ And I commanded you at that time , saying , The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God hath given you this land to possess it: ye shall pass over armed before your brethren the children of Israel , all \add that are\add* meet for the war.\f + \fr 3.18 \ft meet…: Heb. sons of power\f*
But your wives , and your little ones , and your cattle , (\add for\add* I know that ye have much cattle ,) shall abide in your cities which I have given you;

Until the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* have given rest unto your brethren , as well as unto you, and \add until\add* they also possess the land which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath given them beyond Jordan : and \add then\add* shall ye return every man unto his possession , which I have given you. \p

¶ And I commanded Joshua at that time , saying , Thine eyes have seen all that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath done unto these two kings : so shall the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* do unto all the kingdoms whither thou passest.
Ye shall not fear them: for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God he shall fight for you.
And I besought the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* at that time , saying ,

O Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, thou hast begun to shew thy servant thy greatness , and thy mighty hand : for what God \add is there\add* in heaven or in earth , that can do according to thy works , and according to thy might ?
I pray thee, let me go over , and see the good land that \add is\add* beyond Jordan , that goodly mountain , and Lebanon.

But the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* was wroth with me for your sakes, and would not hear me: and the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* said unto me, Let it suffice thee; speak no more unto me of this matter.

Get thee up into the top of Pisgah , and lift up thine eyes westward , and northward , and southward , and eastward , and behold \add it\add* with thine eyes : for thou shalt not go over this Jordan.\f + \fr 3.27 \ft Pisgah: or, the hill\f*
But charge Joshua , and encourage him, and strengthen him: for he shall go over before this people , and he shall cause them to inherit the land which thou shalt see.
So we abode in the valley over against Beth-peor.
